.TH "ata_sff_prereset" 9 "ata_sff_prereset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_sff_prereset \- prepare SFF link for reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_sff_prereset
.BI "(struct ata_link *link "  ","
.BI "unsigned long deadline "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
SFF link to be reset
.IP "deadline" 12
deadline jiffies for the operation

SFF link \fIlink\fP is about to be reset.  Initialize it.  It first
calls \fBata_std_prereset\fP and wait for !BSY if the port is
being softreset.

LOCKING:
Kernel thread context (may sleep)
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno otherwise.
